title: Grateful Dead Live at Edmundson Pavilion, U of Washington on 1974-05-21
description:
Set 1

Me & My Uncle, Brown Eyed Women, Beat It On Down The Line, Deal, Mexicali Blues, It Must Have Been The Roses, The Race is On, Scarlet Begonias, El Paso, Row Jimmy, Money Money, Ship of Fools, Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Weather Report Suite Part 1-> Let It Grow-> China Doll

Set 2

Playin' In The Band, U.S. Blues, Big River, Stella Blue, Around & Around, Eyes Of The World-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: china doll nice show, decent setlist. quality recording. great china doll i.m.o.
NICE EYES. nice set list.  nice matrix.  nice phil solo in eyes of the world.

46 Minute Playing in the Band This is a really great show, the Playin' is massive. The first set has a whacked out set list closing with China Doll. Early Keith and Donna.
A lotta fun...

BIg highlights Not my favourite from 74, which is probably my favourite year but some huge highlights. 
That is one monster Playin'! I found it to be full of peaks and valleys with a few sections that lost my attention but some incredible moments. It;s truly a journey!
The outstanding Eyes is on par with the excellent, jazzy versions from this year. WRS is also special. The Wharf Rat on the other hand, I found disappointing - Jerry's vocals sound very strained (not in the tired, world-weary kind of strained sound he had in his later years).
Great show over all.

40 & more yrs ago right here in Seattle yes, yes, this is one of the greatest shows of all time by one off the greatest bands ever.

today's the day ! Edmundson Pavilion, UW

Keith is especially HOT here out of the gate. check out his solo in BIODTL, & then on Deal he & Jer jam to quite a peak.

& of course, the Playin' ....

Playin' In The Band The entire show is excellent!
This is the longest Playin' they did and best sounding of the nine other same recordings to pick from.
